# Tracing Package

## Purpose

`@dukkani/tracing` centralizes OpenTelemetry setup, context propagation, and tracing utilities.

## Core API

- `registerTracing(config)` for app-level initialization.
- `shutdownSDK`, `flushTelemetry`, and `isTracingInitialized`.
- Utility exports (`withSpan`, `getTraceId`, logger integration, decorators).

## Integration Guidance

- Initialize tracing from app instrumentation entrypoints on the server side only.
- Set `serviceName` per app (`api`, `dashboard`, `storefront`, `web`, or package CLI process).
- Keep OTLP exporter config in environment-driven configuration.

## Constraints

- Avoid direct app imports; this package must remain reusable and framework-agnostic.
- Do not initialize tracing multiple times in a single process.
- Keep production defaults performance-safe (batch exports unless explicitly configured otherwise).

## Best Practices

- Propagate trace context in internal HTTP requests.
- Enrich logs with trace metadata through logger integration helpers.
- Use helper wrappers (`withSpan`, decorators) to avoid duplicate span boilerplate.
